Issues.Body:
* .NET Core Version: 3.0 Preview1
* Have you experienced this same bug with .NET Framework?: Yes


**Problem description:**
Potentially the problem is in case sensitive comparison before registering window class, however I did not find confirmation in documentation that window class name is case sensitive or not.
https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/blob/a83e00a9ae61efa4dd9f529a4a7155de026db88e/src/System.Windows.Forms/src/System/Windows/Forms/NativeWindow.cs#L1440-#L1452

**Actual behavior:**
Exception thrown: 'System.ComponentModel.Win32Exception' in System.Windows.Forms.dll
An unhandled exception of type 'System.ComponentModel.Win32Exception' occurred in System.Windows.Forms.dll
Class already exists
>	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.NativeWindow.WindowClass.RegisterClass() Line 1666	C#
 	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.NativeWindow.WindowClass.WindowClass(string className = "RichEdit50w", int classStyle = 0) Line 1487	C#
 	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.NativeWindow.WindowClass.Create(string className = "RichEdit50w", int classStyle = 0) Line 1517	C#
 	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.NativeWindow.CreateHandle(System.Windows.Forms.CreateParams cp = {System.Windows.Forms.CreateParams}) Line 724	C#
 	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.Control.CreateHandle() Line 5825	C#
 	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.TextBoxBase.CreateHandle() Line 1482	C#
 	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.Control.CreateControl(bool fIgnoreVisible = false) Line 5883	C#
 	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.Control.CreateControl(bool fIgnoreVisible = false) Line 5898	C#
 	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.Control.CreateControl() Line 5850	C#
 	System.Windows.Forms.dll!System.Windows.Forms.Control.WmShowWindow(ref System.Windows.Forms.Message m = {System.Windows.Forms.Message}) Line 13940	C#

**Expected behavior:**
no crash
**Minimal repro:**
1. create a new winforms app
2. add a richedit text box to the form
3. add a new control derived from the RichTextBox that sets classname to RichEdit50w that is NOT spelled in all caps
4. add this control to the form and hit F5
```cs
    public class Class1 : RichTextBox
    {
        private IntPtr s_module;
        [DllImport("Kernel32.dll", CharSet = CharSet.Auto, SetLastError = true)]
        private static extern IntPtr LoadLibrary(string libname);

        protected override CreateParams CreateParams {
            get {
                if (IntPtr.Zero == s_module)
                {
                    s_module = LoadLibrary("msftedit.dll");

                    if (IntPtr.Zero == s_module)
                    {
                        // Couldn't load Richedit 4.1. We'll just let the base class return what it wants.
                        return base.CreateParams;
                    }
                }

                CreateParams cp = new CreateParams();

                cp.Width = this.Width;
                cp.Height = this.Height;
                cp.X = this.Location.X;
                cp.Y = this.Location.Y;
                cp.ExStyle = 0;
                cp.ClassStyle = 0;
                cp.Style = 0x100 /* ES_NOHIDESEL */ |
                           0x800 /* ES_READONLY */ |
                           0x10000 /* WS_TABSTOP */ |
                           0x2000000 /* WS_CLIPCHILDREN */ |
                           0x4000000 /* WS_CLIPSIBLINGS */ |
                           0x10000000 /* WS_VISIBLE */ |
                           0x40000000 /* WS_CHILD */;

                cp.ClassName = "RichEdit50w";

                return cp;
            }
        }
    }

```
